race.comment: Big watch on two of the first starters. RED RABBIT (12) made her debut at odds and after getting back found the line strongly to place. Has upside, a low draw and the claim. Should be winding up strongly again. HAND LUGGAGE (13) showed ability in her first two starts then was well off best latest when she gave a big start and didn't come on. Blinkers added to sharpen the mind and can improve this time. YUKAINA (3) is a nicely bred galloper by Maurice making debut. Has had a host of trials, was gelded prior to the last couple, and is showing good ability. Expected to measure up. CATATOMIC (6) is a former NSW galloper who has had a few starts for the new yard and while yet to hit the frame has ability and looks well placed here.
